# Chat & Conversation UI Standards

Apply these when building or editing chat/conversation interfaces and related UI.

## 1. Flux UI + Tailwind

- Use **Flux** components as the main UI layer (Button, Card, Input, Modal, Icon, etc.) from `livewire/flux`.
- Compose and customize with **Tailwind** utility classes. Don’t replace Flux with raw HTML when a Flux component exists.
- Include `@fluxAppearance` and `@fluxScripts` in the layout; import Flux CSS in `resources/css/app.css` per Flux docs.

## 2. Responsive (Mobile, Tablet, Desktop)

- Design **mobile-first**. Start with small viewports, then add `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` as needed.
- Breakpoints: mobile (default), `sm` (640px), `md` (768px), `lg` (1024px), `xl` (1280px).
- Chat/conversation layout must be usable on all three: e.g. stacked on mobile, side-by-side or wider on tablet/desktop.
- Test list/message width, tap targets (min ~44px), and readable text without horizontal scroll on mobile.

## 3. Icons

- Use **icons** for: send, attach, menu, back, status, actions (edit/delete), and other clear actions.
- Prefer Flux `<x-flux:icon />` or the project’s icon set; keep style and size consistent (e.g. `size` / `class`).
- Pair icons with text or `aria-label` where it helps accessibility.

## 4. Main Colors: Dark Blue & Blue

- **Primary palette**: dark blue and blue as main brand colors.
- Use for: primary buttons, links, active states, headers, key accents.
- In Tailwind: define or use custom colors, e.g. `blue-900`/`blue-800` for dark blue, `blue-600`/`blue-500` for blue; use `@theme` in CSS if you have a custom palette.
- Keep contrast and readability (e.g. white or light text on dark blue, dark text on light backgrounds).

## 5. Animations: Prefer Anime.js

- Prefer **Anime.js** for UI animations (entrance, exit, transitions, micro-interactions).
- Use for: message appear, typing indicator, panel open/close, subtle hover/feedback.
- Keep animations short and purposeful; avoid blocking interaction. Prefer `anime.js` over ad-hoc CSS animations when the effect is more than a simple transition.

## Quick Checklist

- [ ] Flux components + Tailwind used for chat/conversation UI
- [ ] Layout works on mobile, tablet, and desktop
- [ ] Icons used for actions and key states
- [ ] Dark blue and blue as main colors
- [ ] Anime.js used for animations where appropriate
